<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Enable 2FA</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css">
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
      background-color: #f4f4f4;
      color: #333;
      text-align: center;
      padding: 50px;
    }
    h1 {
      font-size: 36px;
      color: #444;
    }
    .container {
      display: inline-block;
      background: #fff;
      border-radius: 8px;
      box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
      padding: 30px;
      max-width: 400px;
      text-align: left;
    }
    .qr-code {
      margin: 20px 0;
    }
    .instructions {
      font-size: 16px;
      line-height: 1.5;
      color: #555;
    }
    .footer {
      margin-top: 20px;
      font-size: 14px;
      color: #888;
    }
    button {
      background-color: #333;
      color: #fff;
      border: none;
      padding: 10px 20px;
      font-size: 16px;
      border-radius: 5px;
      cursor: pointer;
    }
    button:hover {
      background-color: #444;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Enable Two-Factor Authentication</h1>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="instructions">
      <p>To enhance your account security, please scan the QR code below using your authenticator app.</p>
      <p>Once you've scanned the code, enter the 6-digit code from your app to confirm.</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="qr-code">
      <img src="<%= qrCodeUrl %>" alt="QR Code" width="200" />
    </div>
    
    <form action="/user/enable-2fa" method="POST">
      <label for="twoFactorCode">Enter the 6-digit code from your authenticator app:</label><br>
      <input type="text" name="twoFactorCode" id="twoFactorCode" required maxlength="6" pattern="\d{6}" title="6-digit code" /><br><br>
      <button type="submit">Enable 2FA</button>
    </form>

    <div class="footer">
      <p>Having trouble? <a href="/help">Get Help</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>